a_n = 1/(1*2) + 1/(2*3) + 1/(3*4) + ...... + 1/n(n+1)
\frac{1}{n(n+1)}=\frac{1}{n}-\frac{1}{n+1}
a_n=\sum_{k=1}^{n}\frac{1}{k(k+1)}=\frac{1}{1}-\frac{1}{2}+\frac{1}{2}-\frac{1}{3}+\dots+\frac{1}{n}-\frac{1}{n+1}=1-\frac{1}{n+1}
n=1,2,3,4
n=1
a_1=\frac{1}{2}
n=2
a_2=\frac{2}{3}
n=3
a_3=\frac{3}{4}
n=4
a_4=\frac{4}{5}
a_n
